  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering can result in significant criminal penalties, including:\n\n1. Criminal Penalties:\n- Potential prison sentences of up to 20 years\n- Substantial monetary fines\n- Forfeitures of assets involved in the transaction\n\n2. Financial Penalties:\n- Fines can be up to $500,000 or twice the value of the property involved in the transaction\n- Civil penalties may also be imposed\n\n3. Additional Consequences:\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Potential deportation for non-citizens\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like transaction amount, criminal history, and specific circumstances of the offense. Prosecution typically occurs under statutes like the Bank Secrecy Act and Money Laundering Control Act.\n\nPrecise details can vary, so consulting a legal professional for specific case advice is recommended.",
